- - - ( HTTP & FS module ) - - -


** ( Necessity Methods ):

1. Import Library 
{ code }: 
• "const http ( or any name ) = require('http');" // The module in creating a web server 
• "const fs ( or any name ) = require('fs');" // The module in 

{ what is it? }: 
• Imports the http module 



2. Create Server Method
{ code }: "const server = http.createServer((req, res) => { ... });"
{ what is it? }:
• a method that takes in a callback function that handles network requests
• it also returns a server object  


( Properties the createServer() returns are ): 

// Starts to listen to the ports & for incoming requests ( all are optional )
• server.listen(port, [hostname], [backlog], [callback] ) 

// Stop the server from accepting new connections
• server.close( [callback] ) 

// Listen for emited events by the server object after listening ( 'request', 'connection', 'error', 'close' )
• server.on( event, [callback] ) 

// Returns the address and port the server is using
• server.address() 

// Get number of concurrent connections
• server.getConnections( [callback] ) 

// Set default timeout for all connections
• server.setTimeout( timeout, [callback] ) 

// Max number of clients allowed
• server.maxConnections

//  Default timeout for client connections (in milliseconds)
• server.timeout

// returns a boolean, depending if server.listen(3000) is used / not
• server.listening


3. Server ( creatServer returned ) listens to port 
{ code }: "server.listen( 2000 or a variable, callback → runs if listen successful )" 
{ what is it? }: 
• A method that listens to the port in order to start the server 